social_posts.post_text: I’m your biggest fan.👯‍♀️

OUR MISSION: Is to help end the Epidemic of Discontent that exists within our society today. The Epidemic of Loneliness, as the United States Surgeon General call it, is why we are SO passionate about what we do. 

Our CEO & founder @sheisgatzby experienced this herself in moving alone to LA in 2019. Through community she was eventually able to find her own way. 

Now, we at @gatzbys aim to do just the same. Help others through the power of connection & experience. We want you to know, that with Gatzby’s, you are not alone.🦁

Happy moms day to my biggest role model. Thank you for always believing in me (even when I was selling Wonder Bread rolled into balls on the front porch. I am so grateful that you instilled in me your work ethic, drive, compassion & independence. I truly wouldn’t be the woman I am without you & count my blessings every day that I get to be your daughter. I love you mom!🖤

With each @gatzbys experience we have the opportunity to learn & grow so much as a team. Last weekend we learned more than ever within unprecedented circumstances. We sold out the experience last minute which led to technical difficulties that we have now since mended for the future. I am so incredibly proud of this team & all they were able to do to still make this experience the best it could be. As a young startup these moments are even more important than those in which everything goes right, & because of this, I am grateful. On to the next.🦁
Happy Daddio day!☺️

My superlative used to be, “Most likely to be late with a Starbucks.” Although, that may still be true, I am so grateful for the amount I’ve been pushed to grow over the past few years. From my U of A days onward my life has been nothing short of an adventure. So much of which has fed into the creation of Gatzby’s. Today was the last day of (one of) my masters programs, the MS in Innovation & Venture Development at ASU. I am equally as grateful for the academia that now supports the vision this adventure produced. Thank you MSIVD, onto the next scene.🎥✨
